  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "A long, vertical crag around 20 metres high, with some 50 routes graded from 3- to 8. Varied and enjoyable climbing.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:bistaberget"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A long, vertical crag around 20 m high, with some 50 routes ranging from grade 3- to 8. Varied and excellent climbing.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "beskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Description",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Bistaberget, in south-eastern Södermanland, lies in the old mining parish of Tunaberg, just a few kilometres from the climbing mecca of Simonsberget. Bistaberget is a long, vertical crag around 20 m high. Today there are some 50 routes here, ranging from grade 3- to 8. Many of the routes are bolted and equipped with lower-off anchors. Bistaberget also has several fine mixed routes, where the crux is bolted in most cases, while good cracks have been left for traditional protection.\n\nCamping at Bistaberget is not particularly easy, but with a little goodwill there is room for 2–3 tents on the slabs 20 m into the woods from the top.\n\nA guidebook covering Simonsberget, Bistaberget and other crags in Södermanland was published in November 2006. Order from Danger Zone (http://www.dangerzone.se).\n\nDuring autumn 2009, several new anchors were installed and some routes were rebolted. The work will continue in early 2010. More information at http://dangerzone.forum24.se/dangerzone-about18.html.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "If approaching from the north on the E4, take the Nyköping V exit—the last exit for Nyköping. At the second roundabout, turn right onto road 53 towards Oxelösund. Follow signs for Nävekvarn. In Nävekvarn, turn left at the T-junction in the village and continue for about 3.5 km. The crag is beside the road and impossible to miss.\n\nBear in mind that the lay-by by the crag also provides access to the field for the farmer and his tractor. Park considerately.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ovre-vaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Upper Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "lankar": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Links",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A guide provided by Linköpings klätterklubb is available here (http://linkopingsklatterklubb.se/index.php/forare.html).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "routes": {
        "bistaberget-led-1": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Uncleaned solo route. Not fun!",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-11": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts in a crack formation, continues up a small corner, via a ledge and then up the larger jamming crack. Essentially a pure trad route, but crosses the first bolt of Kapten Kroks förbannelse.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-12": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Same start as Kapten Krok, but after the ledge goes straight up past three bolts. Two finish variants, 5a and 6c.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-15": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A very good and varied route. Goes through the obvious alcove and up into a system of corners, cracks and other fun features. The second half is protected by three bolts, one piton and trad gear, with good protection.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-16": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Enjoyable, steep climbing up an obvious crack system. Starts right of the crack leading into the crack system, then traverses left into the cracks via a few crimps. Well protected. Large, sturdy pine at the top for top-roping if desired; bring a static rope.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-23": {
          "description": {
            "text": "The first half is well bolted; the second half takes trad gear. The anchor is some way left, beyond the small pine. There is also a nut-protected finish of the same grade that goes straight up at the end, climbed by Andreas Harne in September 2011. A proper abseil anchor is to be installed on the variant; currently there is a single bolt.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-26": {
          "description": {
            "text": "The grade is disputed. The guidebook gives 7b+, which is very generous. Many consider it closer to 7a+.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-27": {
          "description": {
            "text": "An enjoyable, well-bolted route, apart from the start. Exposed for the grade, with good climbing.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-28": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A very good, nut-protected finish. Follow large holds up the obvious crack.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-29": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Start up Ättestupan, then go straight up at the roof. Follow the vertical crack straight up and build an anchor on the pine. Superb, sustained climbing.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-30": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Start up Ättestupan, but immediately go dead straight up and join Lilla flickan zombie. Fantastic positions.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-34": {
          "description": {
            "text": "The extremely obvious, large crack. Not as easy as it looks, and also quite mossy.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-36": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Somewhat fingery and technical, on rock that is quite unusual for the crag: eroded, rough and limestone-like.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "bistaberget-led-43": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Södermanland’s first 8a.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:bistaberget"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
